beer.beer_description: Colonial's Imperial Stout has been brewed with two separate mashes, using the last worts of the first to mash in the second. This intensifies the fermentables in the beer, yielding high alcohol and big body. A spree of dark malts provide a rich malt base with chocolate and coffee-like character plus subtle caramel and toffee to compliment. Mandarina Bavaria hops were chosen to build on this with citrusy aroma and flavour, a time honoured combination. It's been detained in tank for 8 weeks to develop the complex character. ABV 11.7% and 65 ibu
